[SN]TITLE[SN]
Jack Mackreth: Bury sign Macclesfield Town winger

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
League One side Bury have signed Macclesfield winger Jack Mackreth for an undisclosed fee on an 18-month deal, with the option for a further year.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 24-year-old rejoined the Silkmen for a second spell in June after leaving Tranmere Rovers and has scored once in 26 appearances this season.
Mackreth has also had spells in non-league with Barrow and Grimsby Town during his career.
He could make his Shakers debut in Monday's game against Sheffield United.
Meanwhile, Macclesfield have confirmed the signing of 24-year-old Laurie Bell, who spent time at Manchester City's academy as a youngster before moving to the USA.
